Kaizer Chiefs Football Club has announced the departure of goalkeeper, Virgil Vries. Taking to the Facebook page, the team had this to say "Kaizer Chiefs would like to announce the departure of goalkeeper Virgil Vries. His contract with the Club has been terminated and is effective immediately.The Club wishes him all the best in his future endeavours." The Namibian international goalkeeper, Virgil Vries, was on his way out of the club having fallen out of favour under Ernst Middendorp, and his official departure has now been confirmed after they agreed to terminate his deal with immediate effect. 